<DOC><DOCNO> AP890908-0090 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-08-89 1218EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Bangladesh     09-08 0135</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bangladesh,0138</SECOND><HEAD>Two Students Killed in Clashes Between Rival Groups</HEAD><DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Rival groups of students clashed in twocities, and at least two students were killed and 50 were injured,police said Friday.   The clashes took place Thursday in Comilla, 55 miles east ofDhaka, and in Sailakupa, 80 miles west of the capital.   Police said an unidentified college student was killed when abomb exploded during a clash between members of the IslamicStudents' Forum and the Nationalist Students' Party fighting for thesame rally site in Comilla.   At Sailakupa, fighting erupted when members of rival groupsattacked a demonstration by the Nationalist Students' Party, killingone student, police said.   The groups all belong to political parties opposed to thegovernment. They have been battling for control of their colleges.</TEXT></DOC>